column10:
- the story is a roller-coaster, but most of the time, it's uninteresting;
- the characters are not likeable, neither villains nor protagonists;
- annoying wolves and infected wolves, holy molly...;
- annoying snipers on trees with aim-bot;
- I couldn't care less about the missing wife, and the boring flashback sections;
- good rewarding system, but too slow to progress;
- unbalanced enemy mechanics, sometimes they are a hulk and other times they are as dumb as rock;
- stealth feels good, but way too repetitive and limited;
- the "main" story drags on and on, after a while, I forgot what exactly I was persuing;
- more often than not, the actions that some characters take are way too predictable, but it's no surprise, as the director took inspiration of many zombie series and movies, so I've seen it all;
- some stability issues, in this PC port;
- please, don't force us, the players, to slow-walk some sections, they are annoying;
- escort missions are beyond idiotic;
- the mixture of realism and arcade mechanics are not well thought-out, like Red Dead Redemption 2, to name one example;
- ambience is good and well designed;
- the soundtrack is generic and I had a better time disabling it;

The game is designed to waste as much time as it can. The difficulty will suck you dry. The A. I. of the horde of zombies are perfected to annoy you and outrun you. Fetching resources is a chore and not fun.

The acting is superb, but not enough to hook you into it, most of the times.

Casual difficulties;
Dialogues are trash;
Grinding system is trash;
Main story is trash.
Riding bikes feels nice;
Nice Zombie atmosphere, could add more evo mutants.
Ok gameplay
